page.title: 02GENERAL DESCRIPTION(2)
page.content: They also grow vegetables such as; {marrows,cauliflowers,onions,cabbages, {potatoes,carrots,sugar beet}etc.There are very few hedges and walls as most of the fields are separated by dykes or ditches and drains.These dykes are used for land drainage. Some fields are very wet where old ponds have now been filled in. Our villages are quite busy. We have{Marshall's Produce}which pre_packs vegetables for many large supermarkets, and a large box factory called{Pearson's Packages}which produces boxes and pallets for use in the collection and delivery of vegetables.In{Benington}we have{two} {dancing schools}called{'Dancing Years {Studio'.}The schools are run by Mrs Barbara Brown who is a qualified dancing instructress. {
